body:
Given the following code: https://godbolt.org/z/rzr5We5Px

```rust
trait Tr1<'a> {}
trait Tr2 {}
impl<T> Tr1<'_> for T {}
impl<T> Tr2 for T {}

trait Foo: Sized {
    fn foo<'a, T: Tr1<'a>, U: Tr2>(x: &mut T, y: &U) -> Self;
}

fn bar<F: Foo>() {
    let mut x = 1;
    let x = &mut x as &mut dyn Tr1;
    F::foo(x, &2);
}
```

The current output is:

```rust
error[E0277]: the size for values of type `dyn Tr1<'_>` cannot be known at compilation time
  --> <source>:13:5
   |
7  |     fn foo<'a, T: Tr1<'a>, U: Tr2>(x: &mut T, y: &U) -> Self;
   |                            - required by this bound in `Foo::foo`
...
13 |     F::foo(x, &2);
   |     ^^^^^^ doesn't have a size known at compile-time
   |
   = help: the trait `Sized` is not implemented for `dyn Tr1<'_>`
help: consider relaxing the implicit `Sized` restriction
   |
7  |     fn foo<'a, T: Tr1<'a>, U: Tr2 + ?Sized>(x: &mut T, y: &U) -> Self;
   |                                   ^^^^^^^^
```

Note that in spite of referring to `Tr1` as the problematic type, all spans refer to `Tr2`. This only occurs for trait methods.
